UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1623
1 AN ACT relating to the grocery store initiative fund.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 205 IS CREATED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 (1) (a) There is hereby established in the State Treasury a revolving account to be
6 known as the grocery store initiative fund. The fund shall consist of moneys
7 received from state appropriations, gifts, grants, federal funds, and all
8 repayment, interest, or other return on the investment of fund dollars as
9 required by this section.
10 (b) The fund shall be administered by the Cabinet for Health and Family
11 Services.
12 (c) Moneys in the fund shall be used for the purposes set forth in this section.
13 (d) All repayment, interest, or other return on the investment of fund moneys
14 are required to be returned to the fund and used for eligible activities in
15 accordance with this section.
16 (e) Notwithstanding KRS 45.229, any moneys remaining in the fund at the
17 close of the fiscal year shall not lapse but shall be carried forward into the
18 next fiscal year.
19 (2) The cabinet shall utilize the grocery store initiative fund to expand access to
20 healthy foods in underserved areas by providing grants, loans, and technical
21 assistance to eligible food retailers and food enterprises that are independently
22 owned for-profit grocery stores, cooperative grocery stores, nonprofit grocery
23 stores, or grocery stores owned and operated by local governmental units.
24 (3) The cabinet may place limits on the size of the food retailers and food enterprises
25 that are eligible for grants, loans, and technical assistance, including limits on
26 the annual revenue or projected revenue of the applicant, number of full-time
27 employees, or square footage of the facilities.
