UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1623
1 (4) The cabinet may prioritize grants, loans, public-private partnerships, and
2 technical assistance to applicants based on poverty rates, income, geographic
3 diversity, local ownership, access to grocery stores in the area surrounding
4 proposed project locations, and other factors as determined by the cabinet.
5 (5) The cabinet may make grants, loans, public-private partnerships, and technical
6 assistance awards for one (1) or more of the following:
7 (a) Market and site feasibility studies, promotional materials, and marketing;
8 (b) Salaries and benefits for workers;
9 (c) Rent or a down payment to acquire a facility;
10 (d) Establishing a new grocery store;
11 (e) Capital improvements, planning, renovations, land acquisition, demolition,
12 and durable and nondurable equipment purchases;
13 (f) Upgrades for existing food retailers and food enterprises; and
14 (g) Other costs as determined to be eligible by the cabinet.
15 (6) By October 1, 2027, and October 1 of each year thereafter, the cabinet shall
16 submit a report to the Governor and the Legislative Research Commission for
17 referral to the Interim Joint Committee on Health Services, which shall include:
18 (a) A summary of all grants, loans, public-private partnerships, and technical
19 assistance awards;
20 (b) An account of all funds received and awarded;
21 (c) A summary of all progress on activities funded; and
22 (d) Any recommendations for future initiatives or actions.
23 (7) The cabinet shall promulgate administrative regulations in accordance with KRS
24 Chapter 13A to implement this section.
